      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELARA BALE (1) was a course and distance placegetter (16.17) last time also from the same draw, finishing a 0.8 lengths second in a Grade 4. Has the ability and expected to go close. TEDDY DANGER (3) goes very well here starting 20 times for eight wins and four minors. Scored by 4.5 lengths last time (15.97) in a Grade 5 over 278m at this track. Can feature with the right run. BUCKLE UP EASTON (2) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 16.23 beating It's A Scotch. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. GAWLER GIRL RUBY (8) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
